&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Commercial Manager you will be responsible for maintaining and growing Skyscanner’s Agency Advertising and Direct client revenue in the Japan market, as well as providing support to your team within the wider APAC region across our desktop and mobile sites as well as Skyscanners mobile apps. Tasked with developing existing and forging new relationships you will help ensure Skyscanner achieves optimum share of all budgets and continues to secure new business.&amp;nbsp; In addition, you will ensure display activity on the site or device is implemented efficiently, to deliver the best results.&amp;nbsp; Being a key member of the commercial team at Skyscanner provides amazing opportunities to represent Skyscanner at external events, which will require occasional international travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate professionally with internal and external audiences, coordinating with other functional and support areas, including campaign delivery, sales, operations, product development and billing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nurture and develop existing clients whilst maintaining strong relationships to retain them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate incremental revenues from existing clients by selling additional advertising opportunities, multi-market solutions and long term commitments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively pursue and secure new business and provide accurate forecasts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply analytical skills to understand our clients’ changing business needs. Work to develop and execute advertising plans that position Skyscanner as a strategic partner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor relevant performance metrics and efficiently manage campaigns to focus on activities that grow revenue and ensure client satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively drive the development of commercial services in Skyscanner’s largest markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the on-going definition and refinement of market and channel specific sales strategies, the implementation plans underpinning delivery of those strategies and active input to the continuing evolution of Skyscanner’s products and commercial propositions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify key decision makers within agencies for online and mobile advertising.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Experience Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in selling digital advertising to agencies and clients direct is essential,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An excellent understanding of the digital advertising ecosystem in Japan, including knowledge of ad networks, ad exchanges, re-targeting, RTB, DSP’s and trading desks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mobile advertising sales experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An ability to communicate value and influence customer decision makers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven success in client management or successful consultative or solution-selling experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An appreciation of an international and technology oriented business environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An entrepreneurial spirit that enjoys working in a people-oriented company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driven to get things done and energised by an opportunity to help build up a high growth potential business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with online travel clients/campaigns is a definite plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent Japanese and English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional Asian languages are a plus (Korean would be helpful)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;#LI-CL1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We’re now looking for a Commercial Manager to join our Strategic Relationships team. This is a great opportunity to work closely with our VP Strategic Relationships, Flights. Working with existing and new partners globally, you will support and often attend senior C suite meetings, conferences and internal updates. In time travel will be part of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working alongside the VP of strategic relations and development, you will help plan our senior level partner engagement ensuring this aligns to the partner management framework and partner priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support development of an ongoing engagement plan and process for airline C-levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the preparation for senior level partner meetings including ensuring alignment on meeting objectives, presentations, briefings, alignment on objectives. Following meets, ensure outcomes are documented, aligning with the team on follow ups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting the evolution of our partner narrative, presentations, and assets, accountable for ensuring partner packs are up to date&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development of the industry influencers concept and framework, working with others to bring this to life&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be part of the Power Partner team, owning specific elements of the initiative such as partner talks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with B2B marcomms support the preparation for industry events and conferences including briefs on key individuals and objectives, supporting preparation of conference material such as presentations, tracking event KPIs against objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the view from the runway meetings, documenting actions, ensuring appropriate meeting preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support other areas as strategic relations continues to scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required Skills/Experience:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in a partner or industry facing role, experience of externally representing an organisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid research, tech, organisation and communication skills a must.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and interest in online travel or the aviation industry is preferable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboration, relationship and stakeholder management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong level of written and verbal skills to communicate clearly on opportunities &amp;amp; challenges to internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You take ownership and get things done.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in solving complex problems and managing ambiguity, ability to work autonomously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We’re now looking for a Commercial Manager to join our Strategic Relationships team. This is a great opportunity to work closely with our VP Strategic Relationships, Flights. Working with existing and new partners globally, you will support and often attend senior C suite meetings, conferences and internal updates. In time travel will be part of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
