&lt;li&gt;Experience and interest in online travel or the aviation industry is preferable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboration, relationship and stakeholder management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong level of written and verbal skills to communicate clearly on opportunities &amp;amp; challenges to internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You take ownership and get things done.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in solving complex problems and managing ambiguity, ability to work autonomously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;The Search Operations team is responsible for maintaining high data quality standards across the search platform. As Skyscanner processes gigabytes of data, it is imperative that information that powers our systems instils trust to Travellers and Partners by being accurate, reliable and consistent. They work with internal teams and their data to actively monitor, resolve and improve data conflicts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p-rich_text_section&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Role Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;p-rich_text_list p-rich_text_list__bullet&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;unordered-list&quot; data-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-border=&quot;false&quot; data-border-radius-top-cap=&quot;false&quot; data-border-radius-bottom-cap=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Investigate, manage, and resolve data conflicts using a variety of tools and resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Analyse and interpret raw flight data and present key findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Process change requests into data systems to complete end-to-end resolution of data conflicts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Collaborate with internal teams to prioritise business and information needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Identify and iterate improvements to processes, documentation and, data management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Own ad hoc product analysis for internal stakeholders across the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;#LI-CL1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“In this internet based economy every Software Engineer is a polyglot by necessity. We’re required to switch technologies efficiently, relying on our fundamental engineering skill-set to progress. That’s not to say we should all be generalists, specialists are also needed, but the core and fundamental skills of a specialist can be applied in many technologies&lt;/strong&gt;.”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- Skyscanner Senior Architect &amp;amp; Tribe Lead&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a Software Development Manager at Skyscanner, you’ll be technically leading while managing and developing your team of engineers as you join them in building world class products for our users. We&#39;re looking for technical team managers who are product enthusiasts with proven expertise in leading, managing and developing people towards reaching both their career goals as well as the ever scaling objectives of Skyscanner and a passion for leading and advocating change, innovation and engineering best practice.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are the word’s travel search engine and we’re doing great new things as we engineer at scale. Our technical managers are responsible for leading their teams in the design and development of systems that keep our travel search solutions ahead of the pack. As well as engineers, you will work closely with architects, product and project managers, providing technical leadership to define the roadmap and deliver new features to the market. On top of all of that, you’ll have a hands on role in the planning, execution and successful delivery of state of the art solutions. You&#39;ll mentor our technical staff and be actively involved in recruiting our future engineering talent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You can offer us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A background in software development, proven technical leadership, a track record of inspiring your teammates with your passion and vision, a self-motivated working style, a flexible approach and communication skills in spades.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We can offer you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An excellent career move, the chance to work with and lead a team of ultra smart developers and a great working culture of collaboration and technical excellence. The freedom and autonomy of your own technical choices and what&#39;s more you&#39;ll have the&amp;nbsp;space to be trusted to do what you do best and the opportunity to make a real difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What do you need to apply?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We need your talent and expertise to help us do something great for over 100 million travelers,&amp;nbsp; making booking stays and journeys more sustainable and straightforward. It involves technical challenges and the latest technology, but that’s ok by you – in fact, it’s exactly what you want.As an Engineering Manager, you’ll build a high performing team capable of creating robust, creative products, supporting them with your leadership and management skills. You’ll know all about building scalable systems using cloud technologies and will occasionally get involved with hands on development.As a global team, we have a great diversity of our people, so we would expect you have a good communication skill as well as good English language to collaborate with different people, working with different teams and disciplines together to build great things and turn into success for the company. Since both the business and technology changed frequently, we would also expect you have the fast-learning skill as well as being open-minded to always adapt to the new environment and new challenge you face. Being a manager and leader, we hope that you could not only help the team deliver things in productivity, but also drive the team and individuals for their growth.Already a global leader in travel, we want to elevate the way we work to a whole other level. In return, you’ll get meaningful things like medical insurance, headspace subscriptions, a home office allowance and the option to buy more holiday. You’ll have the opportunity to work from any country for 4 weeks a year, and 30 days in our other global offices. Everything, in other words, to help you relax and give your best.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our tech stack includes (but is far from limited to): Python, Java, .Net, JavaScript, CoffeeScript, Couchbase, RabbitMQ, SQL, SQL Server, Elastic Search, Graphite, AWS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proactive. Passionate. Proficient. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working at Skyscanner just feels… different. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It’s the way we love to collaborate, yet take personal ownership of our work.&amp;nbsp; We’re excited about improving the world of travel and working here isn’t quite like anywhere else. &amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Creating an IT environment with solid and modern technology, to support everyone in the business to do the best work of their lives.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;System administration and application support. Troubleshooting and diagnosis. Automation and scripting. Excellent customer service: You’ll need to have done them all and be a domain expert in at least one to join us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We need someone who can help create and maintain our digital workplace by drawing on your skills and experience while leading and mentoring other engineers. You should be capable of designing and operating systems and services, including open-source, internally built and commercial third-party solutions. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;A passion for learning new technologies and helping others do the same will take you far in this role and great communication and customer service skills will be essential.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We use Endpoint Manager (SCCM/Intune) and JAMF to manage our devices and we are working to develop these systems to improve how we function. We work in Azure, Group Policy and Active Directory. Cloud, automation and zero touch are goals we work towards to improve efficiency, effectiveness &amp;amp; resilience within the organisation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As a Systems Engineer, you’ll help your colleagues to achieve their goals by enabling them with communication tools, applications and devices. You&#39;ll maintain systems and services that make up our hybrid digital workspace and be involved in driving initiatives for improvements. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You&#39;ll support all office staff directly or via technical escalation where required and look into the root causes. You’ll participate in various support rotas, whilst allowing you to work on your projects and goals outside of support as well. At all times you will ensure that jobs are logged correctly within the appropriate ticketing system.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Of course, you’ll also be looking for opportunities to automate repetitive tasks and improve our services. Though you’ll be accountable for the delivery of Squad projects and trusted to deliver, you’ll also form part of a broader team that takes collective responsibility for making success happen..&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Already a global leader in travel, we want to elevate the way we work to a whole other level. In return, you’ll get meaningful things like medical insurance, health screenings, headspace subscriptions, a home office allowance and the option to buy more holiday. You’ll have the opportunity to work from any country for 4 weeks a year, and 30 days in our other global offices. Everything, in other words, to help you relax and give your best.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more details on Engineering at Skyscanner, check our &lt;a href=&quot;https://medium.com/@Skyscannereng&quot;&gt;Engineering Blog&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and follow&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/SkyscannerEng&quot;&gt;Skyscanner Engineering&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;on Twitter&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proactive. Passionate. Proficient. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working at Skyscanner just feels… different. &amp;nbsp;It’s the way we love to collaborate, yet take personal ownership of our work.&amp;nbsp; We’re excited about improving the world of travel and working here isn’t quite like anywhere else. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;auto-cursor-target&quot;&gt;The security tribe at Skyscanner is a cross-skilled function with&amp;nbsp;a deep knowledge of secure software development best practices, web, mobile and cloud security.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&amp;nbsp; build strong relationships with other&amp;nbsp;teams across Skyscanner,&amp;nbsp;and partner to design and proactively integrate initiatives to enhance security across a wide variety of domains and technology stacks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We scale security by empowering teams with awareness, guidance, training and direction, while&amp;nbsp;automating&amp;nbsp;and embedding security in engineering processes. This includes early-stage designs, threat models,&amp;nbsp;code reviews, triaging vulnerabilities, building and integrating security tooling&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;championing security initiatives across Skyscanner&#39;s product and engineering teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is also responsible for preventing cyberattacks, vulnerability research and&amp;nbsp;technical security assessments to highlight risk, promoting security across the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must be self-motivated, expected to demonstrate sophisticated Cybersecurity engineering knowledge, be able to independently resolve approaches to difficult technical problems and communicate broadly across&amp;nbsp;teams and disciplines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will report to our Director of Security,&amp;nbsp;playing a key role in the Security tribe, influencing the vision and roadmap of the team&amp;nbsp;and will regular work on strategic and highly visible security activities&amp;nbsp;aligning&amp;nbsp;with the technical leaders across our engineering, enablement and platform teams&amp;nbsp;to design&amp;nbsp;and set standards and security principles across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;Principalsecurityengineer-KeyResponsibilitiesandCriteria&quot;&gt;Key Responsibilities and Criteria&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Above all, an inclusive, humble and also highly skilled&amp;nbsp;leader that can adapt to change, a rapidly maturing security culture, and an eagerness to guide, mentor other engineers with strong communication skills with a proclivity towards collaboration and building meaningful relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for security,&amp;nbsp;hunting for vulnerabilities and driving remediations.&amp;nbsp;You will a subject matter expert&amp;nbsp;in Amazon Web Services cloud, web and mobile security. You will&amp;nbsp;continuously perform technical security assessments, research, applying or combining&amp;nbsp;existing hacking techniques on an innovative way to discover new threat and reproduce vulnerabilities to Skyscanner web and cloud environments&amp;nbsp;to drive Skyscanner&#39;s security.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, pro-active and autonomous. Collaborate with other engineers to lead and validate security-focused architectures and designs across numerous Skyscanner services, cloud environments and partner&#39;s integrations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coding experience and strong knowledge of the Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC). You will identify and lead opportunities to enhance existing security processes related to product assessments, pen testing, security automation, secure coding practices and bug bounty findings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For more details on Engineering at Skyscanner, check our&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://medium.com/@Skyscannereng&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Engineering Blog&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;and follow&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/SkyscannerEng&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Skyscanner Engineering&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;on Twitter.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;#LI-LM2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll be doing&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Lifecycle Marketing Executive to join our rapidly growing team and help push lifecycle marketing to new heights for our millions of users a month across over 50 countries worldwide. Within our high performing team you will play an active role in developing, executing, and optimising our lifecycle strategy across multiple Skyscanner products and multiple markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is an amazing opportunity for a passionate and collaborative lifecycle marketer to make a significant impact as we develop and evolve our truly customer focused engagement and retention strategy for millions of travellers each month.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership in developing, executing, and optimising parts of our localised email, push and in-app marketing strategies across lifecycle, transactional, triggered, and promotional campaigns with a localised approach in multiple markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with design, product, engineering, translations, and data tribes to design and execute highly efficient localised lifecycle marketing strategies for both web and app users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Focus on testing, personalisation, localisation and automation to drive improved performance and efficiencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute meaningfully to key analyses and reporting for your campaigns and channels, feeding that back into global retention strategy, priorities, and roadmaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage internal data, industry insights, market trends, and the competitive landscape to make data-driven recommendations for continuous improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Obsess over the latest tools and strategies with which to reach potential customers, engage them and increase customer retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own lifecycle QA processes to ensure campaigns and touchpoints are sent out on time and error free.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands on experience with ESP/lifecycle automation platforms is essential, Experience with the Customer Engagement Platform such as Braze is desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execution of a Lifecycle Marketing strategy that converts traffic, increases customer retention and drives business value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of workflows, segmentation, user journeys, personalisation, automation strategies, conversion optimisation and other lifecycle tactics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with app lifecycle marketing including push and in-app notifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of how to improve campaign performance (open rates, click through rates, conversions, etc) through execution of A/B testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience partnering closely with Product and Engineering to deliver high quality platforms, tools, and experiences to support our Lifecycle Marketing priorities &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient with Excel to conduct data analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with analytics dashboard such as Tableau or PowerBI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;#LI-CLI&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll be doing&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;We’re looking for a Lifecycle Operations Manager to join our rapidly growing marketing team You’ll effectively bridge the gap between our program managers, data and engineering teams to own the delivery of the data&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;that enables program managers to personalise emails and push notifications to millions of users a month across 50+ countries worldwide. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Within our high performing Lifecycle team you’ll be responsible for ensuring the data is available in the right format and available in a timely manner to allow program owners to execute on the lifecycle strategy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;This role is an amazing opportunity for an Operations Manager to be at the heart of evolving and executing on our data.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
