&lt;p&gt;As a Principal Staff Engineer, you’ll bring the technical leadership to large scale architectural implementations. This means being able to provide technical guidance, support and drive iterative delivery through thin vertical slices of features to delivered to real users in production… every day. It means clarifying, elaborating and iterating on the Skyscanner engineering technology roadmap and designs. You’ll also collaborate with Principal Engineers in other areas of the business, to influence technical direction across the organisation. It means participating in education, mentoring and/or coaching programs for the wider engineering community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Skyscanner is a place where your senior-level talents will really come into play. They’ll cover areas such as Java, NoSQL databases, SQL, Python, AWS, Kubernetes, Istio.&amp;nbsp; You’ll still be hands on coding, staying up to date with the latest technical trends and languages and be fluent in one or more programming languages. And you’ll be completely comfortable using Agile and Lean methodologies. With these skills, you’ll be an expert in your domain, inspiring teams to think smarter to deliver software quickly and shape our technical direction. Value and quality will be your obsessions: you’ll be a champion for world-class engineering and iterative software delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Who could have predicted what 2020 has brought? Travel has been impacted considerably, but Skyscanner’s unwavering commitment to our travellers and partners remains as strong as ever. We weathered the storm and now moving forward helping our travellers.&amp;nbsp;Skyscanner’s unwavering commitment to our travellers and partners remains as strong as ever. We’re confident that our travellers’ appetite to explore the world will return, and we will need your expertise to help us make travel more sustainable and straightforward, along with all the new considerations of an evolving industry.&lt;/p&gt;
