&lt;blockquote class=&quot;c-mrkdwn__quote&quot; style=&quot;padding-left: 80px;&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;quote&quot;&gt;As a Principal Staff Engineer in Mobile, you’ll bring the technical leadership to large scale architectural implementations. This means being able to provide technical guidance, support and drive iterative delivery through thin vertical slices of features to delivered to real users in production… every day.&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote class=&quot;c-mrkdwn__quote&quot; style=&quot;padding-left: 80px;&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;quote&quot;&gt;It means clarifying, elaborating and iterating on the Skyscanner engineering technology roadmap and designs. You’ll also collaborate with Principal Engineers in other areas of the business, to influence technical direction across the organisation. It means participating in education, mentoring and/or coaching programs for the wider engineering community.Skyscanner is a place where your senior-level talents will really come into play.&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote class=&quot;c-mrkdwn__quote&quot; style=&quot;padding-left: 80px;&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;quote&quot;&gt;They’ll cover areas such as Swift, SwiftUI, Objective-C, Kotlin, Java, Fastlane, AWS, Dagger, Kotlin Coroutines, RxJava, Retrofit, Android Architecture Components – you’ll still be hands on coding and adept at developing, releasing and maintaining native apps, staying up to date with the latest technical trends and languages and be fluent in one or more programming languages. And you’ll be completely comfortable using Agile and Lean methodologies.&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote class=&quot;c-mrkdwn__quote&quot; style=&quot;padding-left: 80px;&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;quote&quot;&gt;With these skills, you’ll be an expert in your domain, inspiring teams to think smarter to deliver software quickly and shape our technical direction. Value and quality will be your obsessions: you’ll be a champion for world-class engineering and iterative software delivery.&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote class=&quot;c-mrkdwn__quote&quot; style=&quot;padding-left: 80px;&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;quote&quot;&gt;Skyscanner’s unwavering commitment to our travellers and partners remains as strong as ever. We’re confident that our travellers’ appetite to explore the world will return, and we will need your expertise to help us make travel more sustainable and straightforward, along with all the new considerations of an evolving industry.&lt;em data-stringify-type=&quot;italic&quot;&gt;For more details on Engineering at Skyscanner, check our &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em data-stringify-type=&quot;italic&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link&quot; href=&quot;https://medium.com/@Skyscannereng&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://medium.com/@Skyscannereng&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot; data-remove-tab-index=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Engineering Blog&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em data-stringify-type=&quot;italic&quot;&gt; and follow &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em data-stringify-type=&quot;italic&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link&quot; href=&quot;https://twitter.com/SkyscannerEng&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://twitter.com/SkyscannerEng&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot; data-remove-tab-index=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Skyscanner Engineering&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em data-stringify-type=&quot;italic&quot;&gt; on Twitter.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
