&lt;p&gt;For more insight into Product at Skyscanner, check out our Product CPO’s blog on &lt;a href=&quot;https://medium.com/@pierosierra/builders-make-the-best-product-people-22fdb8d75dfe#.66xpb63wo&quot;&gt;What Makes The Best Product People&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focused. Supportive. Honest.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Java, Python, Docker and AWS – you’ll be up to speed with at least two of them, and keen to build your knowledge on them all. Our distributed workflow includes Hadoop/Spark, SQL, Airflow and Jupyter. So, as a skilled Software Engineer, your sound tech experience of Agile/Lean methodologies will be vital for continuous improvement.&amp;nbsp; And though the customer rules your world, your team’s important too. You always help colleagues perform at their best and turn big solutions into smaller, bite-sized tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most roles at Skyscanner can be either Full Time or Part Time. We need your expertise to help us do something great for our travellers: make booking stays and journeys more sustainable and straightforward. It involves technical challenges and the latest technology, from machine learning and cloud services to world-class APIs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Software Engineer, you’ll help us develop a whole range of key product features in your area. It involves defining and implementing services that make up a vital sub-system. As you work, you’ll collaborate across other product engineering development lifecycles, learning and influencing. And though you’ll be accountable for your own projects, you’ll also form part of a broader team that takes collective responsibility for making success happen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Already a global leader in travel, we want to elevate the way we work to a whole other level. In return, you’ll get meaningful things like medical insurance, headspace subscriptions, a home office allowance and the option to buy more holiday. You’ll have the opportunity to work from any country for 4 weeks a year, and 30 days in our other global offices. Everything, in other words, to help you relax and give your best.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For more details on Engineering at Skyscanner, check our&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://medium.com/@Skyscannereng&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Engineering Blog&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;and follow&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/SkyscannerEng&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Skyscanner Engineering&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;on Twitter.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;#LI-JB1&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rewarding. Energising. Open.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Java, Python, Docker and AWS – you’ll be up to speed with at least two of them, and keen to build your knowledge on them all. Our Distributed workflow includes Hadoop/Spark, SQL, Airflow and Jupyter. So, as a skilled senior software engineer, your sound tech experience of Agile/Lean methodologies will be vital for continuous improvement. You always base your decisions on solid data and metrics. But while this technical talent is essential, you’ll also need the drive to produce outstanding work. So you’ll break challenges into bite-size tasks, mentor team mates and always demand quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need your expertise to help us do something great for our travellers: make booking stays and journeys more sustainable and straightforward. It involves technical challenges and the latest technology, from machine learning and cloud services to world-class APIs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in our global team, you’ll be in charge of developing a whole range of key product features. That means defining and implementing services that make up a vital sub-system in your area. As you work, you’ll collaborate with product engineers and influence their thinking. Though you’ll be accountable for your own projects and trusted to deliver, you’ll also form part of a broader team that takes collective responsibility for making success happen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Skyscanner’s unwavering commitment to our travellers and partners remains as strong as ever. We’re confident that our travellers’ appetite to explore the world will return, and we will need your expertise to help us make travel more sustainable and straightforward, along with all the new considerations of an evolving industry.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Already a global leader in travel, we want to elevate the way we work to a whole other level. In return, you’ll get meaningful things like medical insurance, headspace subscriptions, a home office allowance and the option to buy more holiday. You’ll have the opportunity to work from any country for 4 weeks a year, and 30 days in our other global offices. Everything, in other words, to help you relax and give your best.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For more details on Engineering at Skyscanner, check our&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://medium.com/@Skyscannereng&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Engineering Blog&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;and follow&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/SkyscannerEng&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Skyscanner Engineering&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;on Twitter.&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;#LI-JG1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focused. Supportive. Honest.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kubernetes, Docker, Python, Java, and AWS – you’ll be up to speed with at least three of them, and keen to build your knowledge on them all! In Production Platform tribe, we leverage software to do systems at scale! You will join a set of teams who build and operate a core technology platform for product teams to run their services across the globe. This includes large scale Kubernetes clusters, core AWS/web infrastructure, operational monitoring, core libraries, CI/CD, and developer tools. We strive to provide a powerful and resilient base that enables other Engineers to focus on delivering outstanding features to our travellers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, as a skilled Senior Software Engineer, your sound tech experience of Agile/Lean methodologies will be vital for continuous improvement. You always base your decisions on solid data and metrics. But while this technical talent is essential, you’ll also need the drive to produce outstanding work. So you’ll break challenges into bite-size tasks, mentor team mates and always demand quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll help us develop a whole range of key product features in your area. It involves defining and implementing services that make up a vital sub-system. As you work, you’ll collaborate across other product engineering development lifecycles, learning and influencing. Alongside being accountable for your own projects, you&#39;ll form part of a broader team that takes collective responsibility for making success happen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most roles at Skyscanner can be either Full Time or Part Time. We need your expertise to help us do something great for our travellers: make booking stays and journeys more sustainable and straightforward. It involves technical challenges and the latest technology, from machine learning and cloud services to world-class APIs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Already a global leader in travel, we want to elevate the way we work to a whole other level. In return, you’ll get meaningful things like medical insurance, headspace subscriptions, a home office allowance and the option to buy more holiday. You’ll have the opportunity to work from any country for 4 weeks a year, and 30 days in our other global offices. Everything, in other words, to help you relax and give your best.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;For more details on Engineering at Skyscanner, check our &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://medium.com/@Skyscannereng&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Engineering Blog&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;and follow&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/SkyscannerEng&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Skyscanner Engineering&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;on Twitter.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;#LI-JG1&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborative. Ambitious. Empowering.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a skilled Software Engineer, you’ve worked on modern front end technologies and have some server side experience. You’re excited by React, Typescript, ES6, Sass/Less, Webpack and npm to name but a few; and have some experience in Node.js, Python, Java, or other server scripting technologies. But what we really need is someone who can build a new front end codebase, so we can scale through development. This isn’t just about having great technical talents, though. We’re also looking for a sense of team spirit, dedication to customers and accountability for your own projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need your expertise to help us do something great for over 100 million travellers: make booking stays and journeys more sustainable and straightforward. It involves technical challenges and the latest technology – but that’s ok by you. First and foremost, it’s about helping with automation and tackling the technical issues. An interest in security, data engineering/ETL, cloud services, real time accuracy and building APIs will definitely help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Full Stack Software Engineer, you’ll be responsible for key service components. Through your work, you’ll define and implement services that make up a vital sub-system in your area. There’ll be the chance to deal with internal customers directly and be the main contact for your team, solving ad hoc queries, providing first line support and handling admin for core ‘off-the-shelf’ systems. You’ll be accountable for your own projects and trusted to deliver, and also form part of a broader team that takes collective responsibility for making success happen. This role is available on a full or part time basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Already a global leader in travel, we want to elevate the way we work to a whole other level. In return, you’ll get meaningful things like medical insurance, headspace subscriptions, a home office allowance and the option to buy more holiday. You’ll have the opportunity to work from any country for 4 weeks a year, and 30 days in our other global offices. Everything, in other words, to help you relax and give your best.&lt;/p&gt;
